Hood
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,1338,1543]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
This 
<taxonomicName box="[208,423,1338,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Panchaetothripinae">Panchaetothripinae</taxonomicName>
genus comprises one species from southern Europe, one from 
<collectingCountry box="[1138,1243,1338,1362]" name="Malaysia" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, and two species that have overlapping distributions between Africa and Southeast Asia. These two are 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1258,1375,1399]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Phibalothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peringueyi">
<emphasis box="[1111,1258,1375,1399]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. peringueyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that is recorded widely across the Oriental region from 
<collectingCountry box="[592,737,1410,1434]" name="South Africa" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">South Africa</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[772,839,1411,1434]" name="Japan" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Japan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<emphasis box="[898,1029,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. l o n g i c e p s</emphasis>
that is found in 
<collectingCountry box="[1216,1319,1410,1434]" name="Australia" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Australia</collectingCountry>
as well as 
<collectingCountry box="[151,331,1446,1470]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, New 
<collectingCountry box="[407,488,1446,1470]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[547,589,1446,1470]" name="Fiji" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fiji</collectingCountry>
. These two are distinguished from each other on slight differences in the colour of the base of the fore wings. 
<taxonomicName box="[571,707,1483,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Phibalothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiceps">
<emphasis box="[571,707,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. longiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed across 
<collectingCountry box="[1032,1135,1482,1506]" name="Australia" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Australia</collectingCountry>
north of Sydney, breeding on the leaves of grasses, but usually only on introduced species.
</paragraph>
